Description:
MOVE IN THIS MAY - CARR DESIGN!
A NOMINATION SALE - $695,000 - STAMP DUTY SAVINGS FOR ALL BUYER TYPES!
A great opportunity has become available within Collingwood's premier development. A boutique selection of only 44 apartments! Ten Keele Street refines and elevates the aesthetic of Collingwoods iconic industrial architecture, offering a functional and understated place for living that is imbued with light, texture and elegance.
Lot 405 has one of the best positions in the building - located on the front East corner of the building! It has outstanding views and lots of natural light. This apartment is in its final stages of the build and anticipated completion is just around the corner.
- Large floor plan 77.1m2
- City views and Dandenong views to the East
- Large kitchen and living - open plan
- Miele appliances: oven, gas cooktop & microwave
- Built in study desk with shelving
- Built in fridge and freezer
- Miele washer and dryer included
- Built in pantry with shelving and drawers
- Bathroom with luxury fittings
- Luxury robes, with built in draws
- Great sized balcony with views perfect for entertaining
- Concealed heating and cooling system in both living room and master bedroom
- Ceiling fans in all rooms
- Double glazed windows throughout
- Premium finishes - marble or porcelain bench tops and wide oak timber boards.
Call now to find out more!
Emily Shaddick 0409 864 551

Description:
-UNDER OFFER-
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Offering a desirable inner-city lifestyle in an ultra-convenient Collingwood position, this freestanding Victorian home showcases a recent renovation throughout its free-flowing single storey layout. It is ideally located strolling distance to Smith Street cafes and restaurants, city trains, trams options, Darling Gardens and Victoria Park community precinct, and provides easy freeway access. Beyond its charming weatherboard façade with bullnose verandah, the arched hallway leads to three large bedrooms including one with built-in robes. Set quietly at the back is a spacious open plan living and dining area, stunning new stone kitchen with Miele appliances including gas cooking, fridge/freezer and a dishwasher, and updated bathroom with a shower over a bath. French doors open onto a private sunny garden, which is great for young kids. Freshly painted inside and out, this replastered home features an extra w/c, separate laundry, storage room, high ceilings, polished floorboards, ornate fireplace and new cornices, blinds, fencing and gutters. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Online Auction
A stunning double-fronted family setting so close to the city is in seriously short supply, until now, as this completely remodelled modern home is that rare cul-de-sac discovery. Prized off-street parking and a picturesque period profile set an exceptional inner-city tone for this spacious 3 bedroom, 3 bathroom double-glazed sanctuary in beautifully landscaped environs featuring entertainment deck and tranquil water feature. The single-level interior is brilliantly styled and brimming with quality. The main and second bedrooms include ensuites, all have built-in robes, and the family bathroom enjoys an indulging spa bath. The huge 68 sqm (approx.) family living and dining area with north and west-oriented sliding doors incorporates a state-of-the-art stone kitchen with stainless-steel appliances ensuring all is in readiness for a daily gourmet feast. Also offers laundry, Sydney blue gum floors, wool carpets, central heating, split-system air-conditioning, security alarm and data cabling. The incredibly convenient position of this outstanding family home is close to Smith & Brunswick Streets, Queens Parade, schools (Gold Street PS), parks, Fitzroy Pool and city-bound transport.
This auction will be conducted on an online platform. To ensure you can participate you will be required to register your interest to bid and we will provide you with the relevant access details. Please contact the listing agent if you have any questions about this process.

Description:
Enviable Lifestyle, Flexible Floor Plan
ALL INSPECTIONS CURRENTLY BY APPOINTMENT ONLY
Reflecting Collingwoods old world charm amidst a diverse streetscape of period homes, converted warehouses and small commercial premises is this spacious semi-detached Victorian terrace with a floor plan that could accommodate 3 bedrooms OR open the bi-fold doors to add to an already expansive living space. The home enjoys a harmonious blend of period detail with modern amenity and enjoys a location walking distance to the diverse cafes of Smith, Johnston & Brunswick Streets, a host of public transport options or simply cycle to any point of the compass desired.
With a sun drenched rear northerly aspect and handsome block fronted facade the home features 2 large bedrooms, flexibility of 3rd bedroom/additional living/formal dining (your choice), full width lounge, bathroom with laundry facilities/ample storage, kitchen/meals with gas cooking and a delightfully rustic decked outdoor area offering built in cabinetry, corrugated water tank and sustainable veggie patches ready to plant out...Whilst were thinking sustainability the home also offers solar HWS and an additional water tank plumbed to the toilet. Add to this ducted heating, lush timber floor plus so much more

Close to Collingwood's newest cafes, CBD transport and East Melbourne parks, this inviting home features polished floors, ample storage, hydronic heating and split-system air conditioning. Description:
State-of-the-art sustainable with top-floor views
Lifestyle inspiration is the essence of this sublime Oxford & Peel apartment showcasing a sustainable 7-star energy rated design, state-of-the-art style and top-floor views. Melbourne is enamoured by the ethical Small Giants and architects Jackson Clements Burrows' collaborative genius encapsulated in this stunning apartment's commitment to high-end designer living with a low carbon footprint. Enhanced by double-glazing, hydronic heating, air-conditioning, video intercom and the building's own solar electricity, the setting is pure luxury with a beautiful light-filled interior and spectacular internal covered terrace. The layout is cutting-edge chic with its 2 superb bedrooms (built-in robes), living and dining room with full-height sliding door, brilliant Miele-appointed gourmet kitchen, stylish bathroom, laundry and oak flooring. A highly sought-after, city-edge opportunity with lift access and communal rooftop terrace, this outstanding apartment is quietly and securely located amidst the cafes, restaurants, shops, parks and trams of the amazing Smith/Gertrude/Brunswick Streets' precinct.
Jellis Craig Coronavirus Update
At Jellis Craig the health and wellbeing of our clients and staff is our highest priority.
In light of the recent Coronavirus outbreak, we are taking measures to protect our clients and staff from coming into contact with the virus, and request that you do not attend an Open for Inspection if you have:
- Tested positive to Coronavirus
- Symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas
- Agreed to any self-isolation conditions
We also ask that you maintain adequate social distancing from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective clients and Jellis Craig sales teams and where possible refrain from touching surfaces within the property. We also appreciate your understanding if you are requested to wait outside to reduce the number of people in the property at a time.
Thank you for your understanding.

Description:
Authentically Urban and Maintenance-free
An authentic inner-urban apartment, generously-sized by the standards of single bedroom homes, this sophisticated residence is positioned for a diverse, city-fringe lifestyle without peer. You or your lucky tenants can walk easily to the edgy street culture of Smith St, to the best Vietnamese food outside of Vietnam in Victoria St, to pristine Yarra trails, to the convenience of Hoddle St buses and trains from North Richmond Station, plus you can happily lose yourself in the refined parks of East Melbourneits all at your doorstep.
Set on the 3rd floor with no upstairs neighbours, the home highlights a galley-style kitchen with timber tone cabinetry, stainless steel appliances and an easy flow from open-plan living to a sunny, north-facing balcony.
A clever alcove study creates extra flexibility adds to the flexibility of living in this home with secure parking, intercom entry, split system heating, cooling and robes in the bedroom.
This is an ideal home for lovers of vibrant city-fringe living with great transport access and for savvy investors who appreciate the value of a maintenance-free home that is central to so much of the very best that Melbourne has to offer.

Secure Luxury Living At 'Smith & Co'

Features include wide oak floorboards, video intercom and split-system air conditioning.

Description:
Prized 2-level penthouse with sweeping mountain views
The penthouse level panorama sweeping across the ranges creates a stunning backdrop for everyday living and sensational entertaining in this substantial double-storey apartment. Set atop of 'Gibsonia' in a prized corner position within its historic solid brick walls, this outstanding 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment delivers superbly designed space, a stylish modern mood and 2 alfresco areas in Melbourne's premier warehouse precinct. Rising to an expansive open-plan living and dining zone with banks of north windows and breathtaking city-to-mountains balcony views, the level is served by a full bathroom (frameless shower) and brilliant kitchen with Siemens/Bosch appliances, stone countertops and smart custom storage. The large main bedroom features its own amazing terrace and ensuite access to the 2nd streamlined bathroom featuring heated towel rails, marble stone finishes and frameless glass shower, while there's also a laundry, split-system heating/cooling, polished hardwood floors, LED lighting, storage and built-in robes. Lift access makes life easy in this secure Foy & Gibson building with storage cage and undercover car space on title. Perfectly located by Smith/Gertrude/Brunswick Streets' fabulous cafes, restaurants and shops, city-bound trams, hospitals' precinct, parkland and the MCG.
Jellis Craig Coronavirus Update
At Jellis Craig the health and wellbeing of our clients and staff is our highest priority.
In light of the recent Coronavirus outbreak, we are taking measures to protect our clients and staff from coming into contact with the virus, and request that you do not attend an Open for Inspection if you have:
- Tested positive to Coronavirus
- Symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas
- Agreed to any self-isolation conditions
We also ask that you maintain adequate social distancing from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective clients and Jellis Craig sales teams and where possible refrain from touching surfaces within the property. We also appreciate your understanding if you are requested to wait outside to reduce the number of people in the property at a time.
Thank you for your understanding.

Description:
Warehouse wow with the ultimate in inner-city ease
Immerse yourself in the inner-urban lifestyle that has it all with this sensational warehouse conversion. Innovative, immaculate and impressively spacious, the interior makes a huge impression with its combination of natural light, warm timber detail and soaring raked ceilings creating a captivating sense of openness and outstanding vertical dimension.
The house-sized layout showcases open yet delineated living and the dining room is anchored by a modern kitchen equipped with stainless-steel oven and gas cooktop, dishwasher and on-trend subway tiled splashbacks adding visual interest. Sliding doors connect to a rear alfresco courtyard for seamless indoor-outdoor living and entertaining. Fronted by a bluestone courtyard, the enormous home office is perfectly positioned to separate your work zone from the rest of the house. Served by a central bathroom, two upstairs bedrooms are enhanced by built-in robes and access to personal balconies.
This eclectic mix of engaging character and modern style also features a carport, utility and powder rooms and split-system air conditioners.
Part of a tightly held boutique complex, its enviably close to vibrant Smith and Brunswick Streets shops, cafés, art galleries, renowned restaurants and so much more, and is just a short tram ride to the city.
IMPORTANT:
With news of the novel coronavirus COVID-19 dominating daily news headlines, Belle Property St Kilda is ensuring it is following official public health advice in the best interests of our team and our clients.
We kindly ask that clients entering our open homes or our office:
Disclose if you have a cold or flu-like symptoms
Disclose if over the last 14 days, you have travelled overseas to countries where there is a travel advisory of do not travel, reconsider the need to travel or exercise a high degree of caution, or if you have had contact with a person who has travelled to such a country. At the time of writing, the six countries in the high-risk categories are: China, Iran, South Korea, Japan, Italy and Mongolia. We respectfully request that travellers returning from these countries follow government-enforced quarantine protocols
Disclose if you, or someone you live with, is in self-isolation because there is a reason to suspect that they have been exposed to COVID-19
Practice good hygiene, including handwashing or applying alcohol-based sanitiser before entering the premises
Avoid touching all fixtures, fittings and furniture within the homes during open for inspections and instead ask our agents to demonstrate the functionality of any devices if required.
As always, we consider our obligations to our team, our clients and our community our first and most important priority and will continue to work closely with our advisors enabling us to remain proactive and measured, with appropriate precaution.
*PLEASE NOTE ALL EMAIL ENQUIRIES MUST CONTAIN A PHONE NUMBER*
**You are invited to step into the property and explore more, by clicking on the relevant links which include video, interactive Floorplans & Interactive Tour to enable kitchen updates using our photo styling tools or to utilise our furnishing and measuring service**

Description:
Another BISI Property Gone... $985,000
Built with a tangible sense of elegance to exacting standards of a Victorian Terrace is this 1990's replica, which is full of promise that you can simply move straight in and enjoy. Its well presented and wonderfully light 2 level layout offers exciting future potential to further modernize if desired.
An independent lower level enjoys a sunny kitchen and dining wing, cozy lounge, guest toilet, laundry and a surprising deep garden with easy off-street parking for 1 or even 2 small cars. The sleeping quarters on the upper level offers 2 double mirrored robe bedrooms, family bathroom and a sweet balcony setting.
Google Maps will confirm it's in a perfect location, sandwiched between Punt Road & Wellington Street for easy access whether you need to go north, south, east or west for work or leisure, or simply enjoy the cafe lifestyle, being spoilt with many options all on your doorstep.
The Power Of Opportunity is All In The Palm Of Your Hands

Description:
Captivating Warehouse-Style Space & Character
Weaving warehouse inspiration, modern style and streaming north light into a completely unique setting, this exceptional two-storey residence ties in brilliantly with the eclectic, exciting and evolving fabric of Collingwood. Standing on the corner of Charlotte Street, this flexible two bedroom home on its own title presents a rare lifestyle opportunity and an excellent investment near sensational Smith and Brunswick Streets' myriad cafes, shops, Yarra River parklands, trails, trams and train station. Surrounded by secluded courtyard garden, a superb sense of space is launched by an impressive entrance leading to an open-plan living and dining area with polished epoxy concrete floor and bifold doors. There's an updated kitchen with Belling double-oven stove, large upstairs bedrooms plus a bright modern bathroom, big powder room and laundry, all kept perfectly comfortable with split-system heating and cooling. An outstanding low-maintenance, inner-city opening that's innovative, inspirational and absolutely irresistible.

Description:
Stunning & sustainable with a park-view terrace
Sip, chat and have fun with friends while gazing directly over the art park to the blue sky beyond from the cafe/bar-style terrace of this brilliant Oxford & Peel apartment. Enjoy the best view of Collingwood, and an amazing city-edge lifestyle, with a clear conscience as this stunning 2nd-floor apartment is sustainable and stylish with a 7-star energy rated design from the ethical Small Giants and Jackson Clements Burrows architects. Double-glazing, hydronic heating, ceiling fans, air-conditioning and solar electricity do their bit while you relax in the state-of-the-art setting featuring entrance hall, 1 beautiful bedroom (custom BIRs), chic 2-way bathroom, living room with fitted dining area and smart stainless-steel topped Miele kitchen. Defined by full-height window/door and external shutters, the terrace with bar bench is set for year-round entertaining while down below is an endless choice of restaurants, cafes, shops and tram routes on Smith and Brunswick Streets. Also offers European laundry, video intercom, secure car space/storage and a communal BBQ terrace.

The lifestyle benefits of boutique living are perfectly presented by this two bedroom townhouse apartment's high-end appointments, north-facing entertainers' balcony and inner-city location.
